I'd say yes. If the CPU is on, then so is the PPU. I am not aware of anyway that the PPU can be paused by a pin or whatever. When you say power-up sequence I assume you mean the reset that the 6502 must do to use the Reset Vector. As for anything before that, then I assume the same. We need Kevin Norton or Brad Taylor to do a check for us (hint, hint).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=191">WedNESday</a> — Wed Oct 18, 2006 6:24 am</p><hr />
